Init creates an empty .drift/state.xml file by saving an empty State via the caller-provided fileio.Session (see fileio.session). NOT idempotent: if StateStore.Initialized() reports the project is already initialized (state.xml exists on disk), Init returns ErrAlreadyInitialized without writing. If Initialized() returns a non-not-found error (e.g. corrupt state.xml), Init propagates that error rather than overwriting. See cli.init_idempotent for the user-facing contract. See principles.specs_are_truth.